title: Maldives Imports
description: Imports in Maldives decreased to 286.60 USD Million in September from 313.60 USD Million in August of 2022. Imports in Maldives averaged 152.40 USD Million from 2005 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 339.10 USD Million in June of 2022 and a record low of 57.30 USD Million in April of 2005. The Maldives mainly imports fuel, aircraft, wood, prefabricated buildings, iron and steel, telecommunication equipment, vegetables and cement. The Maldivesâ€™ main imports partners are the United Arab Emirates, Singapore, India, Malaysia, Sri Lanka, China, Thailand and United States.
